The ossuary house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look inside Gaudi.
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric saurien, the ladder to a vertebral column of dinosaurs and the balconies to open fish guillas.
This is the house Casa Battlo in Barcelona of architect Antoni Gaudi.
Because of its organic forms, the house received from the premises the nickname of House in Os.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, pieces of tiles and mosaics, a façade recalling the scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is fun for the New Art of Antoni Gaudi.
The front facade of the house runs its dream lines, its beautiful colors and textures that remind nature and animals.
In a more detailed observation, the geometry, the rhythm and the order are carefully considered.
In the night the façade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of color brightness is reinforced.
The rounding and torsion of forms also appears within the interior with the same measure.
The wood can be used to copy the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelids and the blades.
The house Battlo, which stands in the Eixample district in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at the number. 43, was born from the construction of a house of 1877 by architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a rich entrepreneur, first insisted on demolishing the old construction and construction of another new but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and better market reconstruction.
But Casa Battlo's idea as a multi-dwelling house was not thought of by Gaudi alone.
Architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is just on its project that decorations are born for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade.
Other artists and creators also worked for the façade.
The joint work for the Casa Battlo household plans began with successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and the park Guell in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The premises named the hot house just after its completion due to its organic forms "the House in Os".
Others, given the specific mechanism of opening windows, called it "the house that dances".
It is said that above the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint Georges the patron of Catalonia.
Other sculpture elements of the building contain hidden religious motives.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time, with aviation events and typical roads.
Their 45-degree inclination seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi did not fully comply with the construction directives at that time and was not allowed to interfere with them.
At the beginning of the construction, he obtained the city's permission to build, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years after the completion the municipal council was horrified and asked for changes.
He did not like, for example, the members of the municipal council that the pillars of the building were imposing on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Joseph Battlo demanded (and obtained satisfaction) permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and the third room and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is divided by a staircase through which you can access to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi is also working on the modern concept of space linkage.
The common part can be connected fully by opening the doors of the halls and the high society can communicate comfortably or be limited to the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi has also received new façades a non-traditional roof and two additional floors.
Gaudi's game with light is also impressive, blue and white glass tiles with which the interior court is decorated and with the light wells.
The two-colour game gives maximum light in all the floors of the house.
It was simply enough to be based on the principle that white reflects more than the shadow that instead absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house that was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund may be visited by each.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and most beautiful apartment available to the public.
Owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued their visits because they found that it was a profitable business and they expanded the field of visits to the common spaces and to the granier, including the roof terraces.
The entrance ticket in the monument is really not expensive and costs EUR 16.50; students, pensioners, groups and card holders have 20 percent discounts.
The sum is, however, above the entry price in the other Gaudi buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic tours, you must quickly find a friend among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
