The European Union changes the rules for obtaining the visa
People must go to the Visa Applicants Service Centres prior to their interview in the Consular Section; the cost of waiting will be reduced.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedure for the processing of visas at the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit to the Visa Applicants Service Centres (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will receive the applicant's biometric information, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will provide some benefits for the aspirants, including the following:
The total cost of dealing with the visa will be lower, no longer will be required to make a payment to obtain an appointment, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the mail service to deliver the document.
The aspirant will make a unique payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visas with request (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors visas.
People who wish to renew their visas should not present themselves in an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only appear in the closer ASC where they will present the documents and be printed.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken into the CSA, applicants who want a second meeting to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain there less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra 26-dollar service rate.
For further information on the new procedure to request visa, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/boletines/sp10101_Visas-FAQs.html
